  "prompt": "Is there any Part time universities in Hamburg where we can pursue MS?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several universities in Hamburg that offer part-time master's programs. While many programs are designed for full-time students, some institutions provide flexible options that may suit part-time learners. Here are a few examples of universities in Hamburg that you might consider:\n\n1. **Hamburg University of Technology (TUHH)**: TUHH offers various master's programs, some of which may offer part-time options or flexible study formats, particularly in engineering and technology fields.\n\n2. **University of Hamburg**: This university provides a range of master's programs. Some departments may offer the possibility of attending classes in the evenings or on weekends.\n\n3. **Hamburg School of Business Administration (HSBA)**: HSBA offers part-time Master's programs, particularly in business-related fields. Their programs are designed for working professionals and often include evening or weekend classes.\n\n4. **Fachhochschule f\u00fcr angewandte Wissenschaften Hamburg (HAW Hamburg)**: HAW offers several master's programs, and some may be suitable for part-time study. It's best to check the specific course offerings and schedules.\n\n5. **ESCP Business School**: This international business school has a campus in Hamburg and offers part-time master's programs, particularly in management and related areas.\n\nWhen considering a part-time master's program, it's essential to check with each institution regarding specific course offerings, admission requirements, and whether they can accommodate part-time study schedules. It's also a good idea to contact the universities directly for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
